.SH NAME
pamsummcol - summarize (sum, average, etc) a Netpbm image by column

.UN synopsis
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBpamsummcol\fP
{
\fB-sum\fP |
\fB-mean\fP |
\fB-min\fP |
\fB-max\fP
}
[\fIimagefile\fP]
.PP
All options can be abbreviated ta they shortest unique prefix.
Yo ass may use two hyphens instead of one.  Yo ass may separate a option
name n' its value wit white space instead of a equals sign.

.UN description
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This program is part of
.BR Netpbm (1)
.
.PP
\fBpamsummcol\fP readz a Netpbm image (PNM or PAM) n' performs a
summary function over all tha rows up in each column (sum, mean, etc.).
It produces a image of tha same kind dat tha same width n' depth as
the input, n' one row high.  Its sample joints is tha result of the
summary.
.PP
\fBpamsummcol\fP performs tha summary operation on each plane
independently.
.PP
\fBpamsummcol\fP performs tha operation on tha actual sample joints,
not on tha light intensitizzles represented by dem up in tha case dat the
image be a PGM or PPM image.
.PP
If you wanna summarize by row instead of by column, run tha input
all up in \fBpamflip\fP first (and if you want tha output ta be a single
column instead of a single row, use \fBpamflip\fP again).
.PP
If you wanna summarize over tha entire image (gettin a one-tuple
output image), use \fBpamsumm\fP ta git a summary row, \fBpamflip\fP
to turn dat tha fuck into a cold-ass lil column, tha \fBpamsumm\fP again n' again n' again ta summarize the
column.
.PP
If you wanna summarize tha individual samplez up in a entire image,
instead of by tuple, use \fBpamsumm\fP.
.PP
\fBpamsummcol\fP performs tha operation on tha actual sample joints,
not on tha light intensitizzles represented by dem up in tha case dat the
image be a PGM or PPM image or PAM equivalent.  Yo ass can use
\fBpnmgamma\fP ta convert such a image ta one wit samplez proportional
to light intensity, n' then use \fBpamsummcol\fP on tha result.
.PP
Yo ass can big up tha same thang as \fBpamsummcol -mean\fP with
\fBpamscale\fP.  Just scale vertically ta a single row, without scaling
horizontally at all.  Use tha pixel mixin method.


.UN options
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Yo ass must specify exactly one of \fB-sum\fP, \fB-mean\fP,
\fB-min\fP, or \fB-max\fP.


.TP
\fB-sum\fP
.sp
This option make tha summary function addition.
     In each column n' plane of tha output row, tha sample value is the
     sum of all tha samplez joints up in tha same column n' plane of tha input.
     If a result is pimped outa than tha image maxval, it is clipped to
     tha maxval.

.TP
\fB-mean\fP
.sp
This option make tha summary function arithmetic mean.
     In each column n' plane of tha output row, tha sample value is the
     mean of all tha samplez joints up in tha same column n' plane of tha input.

.TP
\fB-min\fP
.sp
This option make tha summary function arithmetic minimum.
     In each column n' plane of tha output row, tha sample value is the
     minimum of all tha samplez joints up in tha same column n' plane of
     tha input.

.TP
\fB-max\fP
.sp
This option make tha summary function arithmetic maximum.
     In each column n' plane of tha output row, tha sample value is
     tha maximum of all tha samplez joints up in tha same column and
     plane of tha input.



